{"word":"H3925 - לָמַד - lâmad - law-mad' - Accustomed","slug":"H3925","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">לָמַד</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>lâmad"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>law-mad'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Accustomed"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05DC;&#x05DE;&#x05D3; - la&#x0302;mad</b> - <i>law-mad'</i><p/>A primitive root; properly to <i>goad</i>, that is, (by implication) to <i>teach</i> (the rod being an Oriental <i>incentive</i>): - [un-] accustomed, X diligently, expert, instruct, learn, skilful, teach (-er, -ing)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H3927\">H3927</a>, <a href=\"#/H3928\">H3928</a>, <a href=\"#/H3929\">H3929</a>, <a href=\"#/H4451\">H4451</a>, <a href=\"#/H8527\">H8527</a>"}]}